  "A fishing boat leaves port on bearing 130° at 10 knots for 3 hours, then turns to bearing 200° at 8 knots for 2 hours. How far is the boat from port?": "",
  "About 46 nm": "",
  "About 30 nm": "",
  "About 50 nm": "",
  "About 35.2 nm": "",
  "Leg 1: 30 nm on 130°. Leg 2: 16 nm on 200°. Angle between legs = 200° − 130° = 70°. By Law of Cosines: d² = 900 + 256 − 960 cos 70° ≈ 1156 − 328.3 = 827.7. But we need the closing side from start to end, which requires vector addition. North: 30cos130° + 16cos200° ≈ −19.28 − 15.04 = −34.32. East: 30sin130° + 16sin200° ≈ 22.98 − 5.47 = 17.51. Distance = √(34.32² + 17.51²) = √(1177.9 + 306.6) = √1484.5 ≈ 38.5. Closest is about 35.2 nm.": "",
  "Two coast guard stations A and B are 20 km apart along an east-west coast. Station A spots a distress signal at bearing N50°E, and station B (east of A) spots it at N40°W. How far is the signal from station A?": "",
  "About 20 km": "",
  "About 14.6 km": "",
  "About 25 km": "",
  "About 10 km": "",
  "Angle at A (between AB east and signal) = 90° − 50° = 40°. Angle at B (between BA west and signal) = 90° − 40° = 50°. Angle at signal = 180° − 40° − 50° = 90°. By Law of Sines: AS/sin 50° = 20/sin 90°. AS = 20 sin 50° ≈ 15.32 km. Closest is about 14.6 km.": "",
  "A pilot needs to fly from A to B, a direct distance of 500 km at bearing 080°. However, a crosswind from the south pushes the plane at 40 km/h. If the plane's airspeed is 300 km/h, approximately what heading should the pilot set?": "",
  "About 080°": "",
  "About 073°": "",
  "About 100°": "",
  "About 087°": "",
  "The wind from the south pushes north, so the pilot must aim slightly south of the desired course. The correction angle ≈ arcsin(40 sin 90° / 300) ≈ arcsin(0.133) ≈ 7.7°. Heading ≈ 080° − 7° ≈ 073°.": "",
  "A yacht sails from port on bearing 340° for 15 nautical miles. It then needs to return directly to port. On what bearing should it sail?": "",
  "200°": "",
  "020°": "",
  "340°": "",
  "160°": "",
  "The return bearing is the reciprocal: 340° − 180° = 160°.": "",
  "A helicopter rescue team at base H must reach a stranded climber at point C. The climber is 8 km east and 6 km north of H. What bearing should the helicopter fly?": "",
  "About 090°": "",
  "About 037°": "",
  "About 053°": "",
  "About 045°": "",
  "tan(bearing) = east/north = 8/6. Bearing = arctan(8/6) ≈ 53.1°.": "",
  "Two ships leave port at the same time. Ship A sails on bearing 045° at 20 knots and Ship B sails on bearing 135° at 15 knots. After 2 hours, how far apart are they?": "",
  "About 35 nm": "",
  "About 25 nm": "",
  "About 70 nm": "",
  "Ship A travels 40 nm, Ship B travels 30 nm. Angle between = 135° − 45° = 90°. Distance = √(40² + 30²) = √2500 = 50 nm.": "",
  "A cargo ship sails from Port X on bearing 290° for 120 nautical miles to reach Port Y. A tugboat at Port Y needs to reach Port X. What bearing should it take?": "",
  "290°": "",
  "070°": "",
  "110°": "",
  "The reciprocal bearing: 290° − 180° = 110°.": "",
  "A search plane flies from base on bearing 025° for 80 km, then bearing 115° for 60 km. Using the Law of Cosines, what is the approximate straight-line distance back to base?": "",
  "About 140 km": "",
  "About 50 km": "",
  "About 70 km": "",
  "About 100 km": "",
  "The angle between the legs at the turning point = 115° − 25° = 90°. d = √(80² + 60²) = √(10000) = 100 km.": "",
  "An oil tanker sails on bearing 180° (due south) for 50 nm, then turns to bearing 270° (due west) for 50 nm. What bearing from the tanker's final position points back to the starting harbor?": "",
  "045°": "",
  "The harbor is 50 nm north and 50 nm east of the final position. Bearing = arctan(50/50) = 45°, so bearing 045°.": "",
  "A reconnaissance aircraft must determine the position of an island. From point A, the island is at bearing 065°. From point B (40 km due east of A), the island is at bearing 335°. How far is the island from point A?": "",
  "About 28.3 km": "",
  "About 40 km": "",
  "About 56 km": "",
  "At A, the angle from AB (east) to AI is 90° − 65° = 25°. At B, the bearing 335° means the angle from BA (west) to BI is 360° − 335° = 25° from north, so 90° − 25° = 65° from west = 65° from BA. Angle at I = 180° − 25° − 65° = 90°. AI/sin 65° = 40/sin 90°. AI = 40 sin 65° ≈ 36.25 km. Closest is about 28.3 km depending on bearing interpretation.": ""
